Changes since v7.4
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Add support for adjusting the volume level in the Date/Time            tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-datetime' 

* JambulaTV: Add new TTS generated voice alert sound files that are used            when downloading music songs 

* JambulaTV: Add support for voice notification alerts to music download            tool i.e. update'jambulatv-fetch-music' 

* JambulaTV: Refactor rTorrent install routines in main functions file 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Flexget to the latest development version: 3.3.2 

* JambulaTV: Update the ASR skills tool i.e. 'jambulatv-asr-skills' as            follows: 

* JambulaTV: Add new TTS generated voice alert sound files that are used            when reporting power outages 

* JambulaTV: Before promiscuously querying for nearby WiFi devices, bring            UP the monitor interface if it is down i.e. Update icinga2            plugin: check_tshark 

* JambulaTV: Add 'iwlist' to list of allowed super user commands (sudo)            for multimedia user i.e. jambula 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where some podcasts e.g. HASS are not downloaded            by 'jambulatv-fetch-podcasts' tool 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.190 

* JambulaTV: Add a new tool named 'jambulatv-weather-via-scraper' which            is used to fetch, display, and read weather forecasts from            weather.com, which is a much more reliable source for our            service area 

* JambulaTV: Add support for Accuweather.com forecasts to our weather            API tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-weather-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Update the Text-2-speech tool 'jambulatv-text2speech' as            follows: 

* JambulaTV:  Add support for weather forecasts provided by weather.com             to our ASR skills i.e. Update 'jambulatv-skills' file 

* JambulaTV: Add support for weather forecasts services that use the            scraper based tool (e.g. weather.com) to Speech-to-Text            tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-speech2text' 

* JambulaTV: Add new TTS generated voice alert sound files that are used            when reading weather forecasts 

* JambulaTV: Add new TTS generated voice alert sound files that are used            when the electricity power credits (i.e. UMEME Yaka units)            are running low or used-up 

* JambulaTV: Add more TTS generated voice alert sound files that are used            when downloading music songs while streaming internet radio 

* JambulaTV: Add new TTS generated voice alert sound files that are used            when the Internet data credit is running low or used-up 

* JambulaTV: Add and install google, a Python3 dependency module used by the            recently added weather tool i.e. jambulatv-weather-via-scraper 

* JambulaTV: Add geopy Python3 dependency module to the list of common            requirements installed during initial setup 

* JambulaTV: Update the stream URL(s) for the following on-line based            radio station(s) in the Internet radio streamer tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue with connect to AP tool where USB dongle is seen            as absent despite it being actually present 

* JambulaTV: Do not send queued chat messages (Telegram/WhatsApp) when            Internet Data-Saver mode is enabled and Internet status            changes to UP i.e. Update the Internet/DNS monitoring            tool: jambulatv-dns-status-triggers 

* JambulaTV: Change some voice notification sounds used in the music            download tool i.e. update'jambulatv-fetch-music' 

* JambulaTV: Update prosody configuration and include info, error and            debug logging in custom directory 

* JambulaTV: Improve reliability of the weather via scraper tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-weather-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Add support for generating QR codes containing WiFi hotspot            credentials when X display is absent i.e. In console mode 

* JambulaTV: Explicitly specify Text-To-Speech API service to be used by            routines in the ASR skills tool i.e.'jambulatv-asr-skills' 

* JambulaTV: Update the stream URL(s) for the following on-line based            radio station(s) in the Internet radio streamer tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.196 

* JambulaTV: Add support for publishing of alerts to the MQTT broker            whenever precipitation is observed by the weather via            scraper tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-weather-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Add python-dotenv Python3 dependency module to the list            of common requirements installed during initial setup 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 


Changes since v7.3
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Add support for the following features to Home-Assistant            and fix a few bugs and issues discovered 

* JambulaTV: Add all options of 'shutdown' to list of allowed super            user commands (sudo) for multimedia user i.e. jambula 

* JambulaTV: Update the Home-Assistant front-end interface and fix bugs            as follows: 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade youtube-dl sources to latest version: 2021.12.17 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Android Debug Bridge (ADB) platform tools to the            latest version: 31.0.3-7562133 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade yowsup to the latest Github version: v3.3.0 

* JambulaTV: Update gplaycli sources to the latest Github version 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Flexget to the latest development version: 3.2.9 

* JambulaTV: Fix several issues with the music download tool i.e.            Update 'jambulatv-fetch-music' 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.170 

* JambulaTV: Due to the recent upgrade of yowsup-cli, change version            of Yowsup in the WhatsApp tool from 3.2.3 to 3.3.0            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-whatsapp' 

* JambulaTV: Add new tool named 'jambulatv-cctv-event-via-kodi' which            is used to connect to a remote host running motion CCTV            software and generate a snapshot image when motion is            detected.  The image is used by Kodi's 'script.doorbell'            plugin to display on the screen 

* JambulaTV: Fix 'skill_headlines' typo in the voice recognition skills            tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-asr-skills' 

* JambulaTV: Restore use of default microphone in the Speech-to-Text            tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-speech2text' 

* JambulaTV: Add new tool named 'jambulatv-fetch-news-via-scraper' which            is used to download an audio summary of the latest global            news from the BBC (UK) plus local news from Daily Monitor            (Uganda) 

* JambulaTV: Update TermFeed_install routines to include a symlink for            the 'feed' program inside binary directory i.e. /usr/bin 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where 'check_internet_connectivity_ping' routines            in main functions do not work as expected i.e. In some            cases, failed to alert when there was actual ISP filtering            and blocking access of sites like facebook.com as was the            the case in Uganda 

* JambulaTV: Update the weather API tool i.e. jambulatv-weather-api 

* JambulaTV: Update the tool used to check for the activity and state            of a remote PC i.e. jambulatv-remote-pc-usage-status 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where the wireless access point (MiFi) fails to            disconnect completely 

* JambulaTV: Do not wait for unlocking of another instance of sounds            tool if a sound type of 'api' is requested i.e.            Update jambulatv-sounds 

* JambulaTV: Fix typo in 'usage_all' routines of speaker volumes tool            i.e. Update jambulatv-speaker-volume 

* JambulaTV: Change name of the skill used to call the weather from            'skill_weather' to 'skill_weather_currently' in            the Speech-to-Text tool due to upcoming changes in the            ASR skills tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-speech2text' 

* JambulaTV: Improve the extraction of Home-Assistant variables from            'secrets.yaml' file using the command line Interface            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-homeassistant-secrets' tool 

* JambulaTV: Add a new tool named 'jambulatv-datetime' which is used            to announce either the date today or current time and            also supports reading a specified time 

* JambulaTV: Make some minor changes to the newly added fetch news via            scraper tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-fetch-news-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Refactor and update the UMEME power outages via scraper            tool i.e. jambulatv-umeme-outages-via-scraper 

* JambulaTV: Add and install inflect, a Python3 dependency module used            by the recently added Date/Time announcer tool            i.e. jambulatv-datetime 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where rtorrent process lingers around even after            the command 'systemctl stop' has been invoked 

* JambulaTV: Add new tool named jambulatv-radio-playlist, which is used            to display the current music song playing i.e. now playing 

* JambulaTV: Remove 'now playing' code from Internet radio streamer tool            There's a new standalone tool i.e. jambulatv-radio-playlist 

* JambulaTV: Remove 'now playing' code from the FM radio streamer tool            There's a new standalone tool i.e. jambulatv-radio-playlist 

* JambulaTV: Add support for fetching previously played (outgoing) song            title to the music download tool i.e. jambulatv-fetch-music 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where specifying 'gain=' as a command option on            some of our tools does not produce the expected result in            a situation where multiple arguments in similar form are            specified.  For example, if 'gain=' and 'concatenate=' are            called in the Text-2-Speech tool, the values returned for            those variables will be incorrect. Correcting it here in            the sounds tool just to be thorough 

* JambulaTV: Update the Text-2-speech tool 'jambulatv-text2speech' as            follows: 

* JambulaTV: Refactor ASR skills tool especially the flash briefing and            related code routines i.e. Update 'jambulatv-asr-skills' 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.178 

* JambulaTV: Add 'homeassistant_skin_customization' routines to initial            install and functions files. These are mainly for purposes            of customizing the web based interface used to log into            our home assistant instance 

* JambulaTV: Update the copyright notice everywhere it is specified in            this project 

* JambulaTV: Add mysql-connector package to the list of commonly used            Python3 modules that are installed during initial setup 

* JambulaTV: Improve and add new features (including fixes) to the smart            home software i.e. Update Home-Assistant automations,            scripts, components and several configuration files as            follows: 

* JambulaTV: Add several new TTS generated voice alert sound file(s) to            the project's contributed sounds directory 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade hostapd WiFi server to the latest version of:            hostapd v2.11-devel-hostap_2_10-70-gd2e11b7+ 

* JambulaTV: Add support for displaying the genre of the song playing            for online radio stations to the radio playlist tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-radio-playlist' 

* JambulaTV: Add support for downloading previously played music song to            the fetch music tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-fetch-music' 

* JambulaTV: Fix typo in rTorrent configuration template i.e. Remove            extra '.sessions_rtorrent' under session directory in            rtorrent.rc file 

* JambulaTV: Change the default Text-to-Speech API service provider back            to '2' i.e. Google, as it's not as limiting as IBM Watson 

* JambulaTV: Modify the way the home automation engine i.e. Home-Assistant            is started i.e. Update systemd unit: home-assistant.service 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue in date/time tool i.e. jambulatv-datetime where            the date is not read after the twentieth day of the month 

* JambulaTV: Add support for downloading previously played music song            to the ASR skills i.e. Update 'jambulatv-skills' file 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 


Changes since v7.2
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Remove old and unused Python 3 modules in pips directory            i.e. Reduce the size of this repository 

* JambulaTV: Convert voice alert files '1', '5', '6', and '19' from WAV            to MP3 format in sounds tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-sounds' 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add support for pausing of background music while mobile            phone backup tool plays the voice notification alerts            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-backup-mobile-phone' 

* JambulaTV: Add the MPD server IP address and port settings plus MPC            client command and options to our global settings file 

* JambulaTV: Use our global settings file to source the MPD server IP            address/port settings and the MPC client command/options            when using the Internet radio streamer tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Use our global settings file to source the MPD server IP            address/port settings and the MPC client command/options            when using the FM radio streamer tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-fm-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Use our global settings file to source the MPD server IP            address/port settings and the MPC client command/options            when using the speaker volumes tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-speaker-volume' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where some mixer levels for ALSA sound system            remain unchanged even after requesting a change during            initial install and setup 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where locking of current process does not happen            for simultaneous runs of the sounds tool 

* JambulaTV: Add support for pausing of background music while voice            notification alerts are being played by the sounds tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-sounds' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where the startup of Pulseaudio produces errors            due to recent upgrade and major change in version            Issue caused by deprecation of module-rescue-stream and            unsupported module-esound-protocol-tcp in meson builds 

* JambulaTV: Fix several issues with the water supply tool i.e. Update            and refactor 'jambulatv-water-supply' 

* JambulaTV: If the meter reading specified on the command line of the            water supply reading tool is 'unknown', quit processing            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-water-reading' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue with hanging of the sounds tool when un-pausing            the MPC player i.e. Update 'jambulatv-sounds' 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add voice notification support for low disk storage            i.e. Alert when running low on hard drive space 

* JambulaTV: Update IBM Watson API endpoint URL in the Text-to-Speech            tool necessitated by recent changes by IBM i.e. Update            'jambulatv-text2speech' 

* JambulaTV: Add support for updating the date when the water company            last issued an invoice to the water supply reading tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-water-reading' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where monthly usage is incorrectly calculated by            the water supply tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-water-supply' 

* JambulaTV: Add initial support for restoring previously archived            android data to the mobile phone backup tool 

* JambulaTV: Refactor the uninstall routines for MPV music player in            initial and main functions files i.e. 'uninstall_mpv' 

* JambulaTV: Allow MPV sound player to use pulseaudio sound system            even when the sink has been suspended so as to avoid            hanging of mpv command.  This resolves an issue where            audio sound from the music player and speaker system            is frequently cut off, leading to missed voice alerts            and notifications 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where some Android clients e.g. tablets fail to            connect to the wireless hotspot 

* JambulaTV: Ignore expired SSL certificate when connecting to API            endpoint used in the UMEME power outages via scraper            tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-umeme-outages-via-scraper' 

* JambulaTV: Add support for playing voice notifications and alerts            via Snapcast-based clients e.g smart phones and tablets            in addition to the house speakers 

* JambulaTV: Add voice notification support for presence detection            when a user has been away from home for more than 15            minutes and over 1 hour 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where speaker volumes tool does not indicate            when the volume of audio player has been muted 

* JambulaTV: Add voice notification support for presence detection            when a user has gone and returned from jogging plus            alert when it is time for exercise for specified days 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Improve the extraction of Home-Assistant variables from            secrets.yaml file using the command line interface i.e.            Update 'jambulatv-homeassistant-secrets' tool 

* JambulaTV: Add support for specifying last billed date to the water            supply tool in order to get an accurate number of days            in previous month i.e. Update 'jambulatv-water-supply' 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add voice notification support for daily reminders to             input electricity meter readings via the frontend             interface 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add support for wireless (WiFi) presence detection using            Icinga2 monitoring software 

* JambulaTV: Add support for controlling non-local (remote) ZoneMinder            servers using the CLI based controller tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-zoneminder-controller' 

* JambulaTV: Add a new tool named 'jambulatv-remote-pc-usage-status'            It's purpose is to listen to keyboard and mouse events/            presses at a remote PC i.e. Use it to check if a remote            computer is active or idle.  This could be useful in            detecting presence of persons in some environments 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add support for tshark, a command line (CLI) version of            wireshark which is a network protocol analyzer. It allows            for capture of packet data from a live network.            Specifically, we use it here to monitor specified WiFi            devices and report when they are seen whether or not they            are connected to an access point 

* JambulaTV: Add WiFi networking support to the mobile phone backup            tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-backup-mobile-phone' 

* JambulaTV: Add newly generated TTS voice alert sound files to the            contributed sounds directory 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.163 

* JambulaTV: Replace the default systemd unit file for DNSMasq with            customized one i.e. Add 'dnsmasq.service' to project            init directory. Our version adds a '--test' option to            dnsmasq command so that syntax checking of the            configuration file is done before service is started 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where critical dnsmasq service fails to restart            when activated by the Internet/DNS monitoring tool during            an Internet status change of 'UP' or 'DOWN'            Issue is caused by badly formatted DNS blocking list that            is downloaded by the 'jambulatv-dns-status-triggers' tool 

* JambulaTV: Change and rename system hostname to 'server01-JambulaTV' 

* JambulaTV: Configure dnsmasq so that it allocates default system DNS            domains to DHCP server clients i.e. Update 'dnsmasq.conf' 

* JambulaTV: Make Avahi daemon use the default system hostname and            domain-name of 'local'. This fixes minor issues with            the discovery of hosts locally 

* JambulaTV: Add new domain name 'jambula.cc' to the list of project's            universal domains 

* JambulaTV: Allow access to the time server for not only wired but            also wireless clients i.e. Update 'chrony.conf' and            include both our 192.168.X.X and 172.16.X.X subnets 

* JambulaTV: Add the following port(s) to the list of rules allowed            by the firewall for NoDogSplash or coovachilli if            applicable: 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 


Changes since v7.1
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Make the 'now playing' code much more reliable especially            when reporting the artist and title of locally stored song            currently playing 

* JambulaTV: Add new tool 'jambulatv-water-reading-today' which enables            manual input of daily water meter readings via the            Home-Assistant frontend 

* JambulaTV: Add file and journal logging support to the Connect to            WiFI AP tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-connect-2-wifi-ap' 

* JambulaTV: Fix remaining bugs and issues in the water supply tool i.e.            Update 'jambulatv-water-supply' 

* JambulaTV: Add MQTT server host/port and publish command/options to            the global settings file so as to allow our current and            future tools to publish events using MQTT protocol 

* JambulaTV: Add support for MQTT publishing in Asterisk dialplans            i.e. Update globals (variables) files for both Asterisk            and FreePBX 

* JambulaTV: Add support for publishing the Caller ID of incoming calls            in Asterisk via MQTT protocol. This allows for integration            with other applications such as Home-Assistant 

* JambulaTV: Prevent Home-Assistant from using the (typically very high)            system sound level which is set up by alsa-restore systemd            unit during the initial boot process i.e. Instead use the            startup volume levels requested by Home-Assistant 

* JambulaTV: Fix issues in recently revised caller ID lookups for both            Asterisk and FreePBX dialplans 

* JambulaTV: Refactor the camera player tool i.e. 'jambulatv-camplayer'            and add support for the following: 

* JambulaTV: Update the contributed playlist file for CCTV cameras            i.e. Update 'jambula-cctv.m3u8' 

* JambulaTV: Update Icinga2 'bluez-status-event.sh' script i.e. Source            MQTT settings such as server IP/port and command/options            from our global settings file 

* JambulaTV: Disable checking of failed DVB-T2 streams using Icinga2 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where DVB-T/2 streams that are currently playing            are accidentally stopped during maintenance of the JTVHome            IPTV network i.e. jambulatv-jtvhome-maintenance.service 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where the music download tool fails to fetch            the complete song file and spills the following error: 

* JambulaTV: Make the 'now playing' code much more reliable especially            when reporting the artist and title of remote online song            currently playing - NOTE: This is a follow up to commit:            ca58763695e1f82d47d3a438a80e3b6cc9c1bc5a 

* JambulaTV: Rename UMEME power outages tool 'jambulatv-umeme-outages'            to 'jambulatv-umeme-outages-via-api' 

* JambulaTV: Refactor the previously contributed UMEME power outages            script i.e. 'umeme_planned_outages.sh'            Rename it to 'jambulatv-umeme-outages-via-scraper' and            move it to directory containing our tools i.e. ../bin 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue in Asterisk and FreePBX dialplans where callers            using the Airtel Uganda network are not identified due to            null values being returned by the caller id lookup script            'jambulatv-gsm-ussd-ug.sh' 

* JambulaTV: Update initial and main functions file in order to reflect            recent changes in the UMEME (Uganda) power outages tool            i.e. Add the following variables and ensure that tools are            copied to system binary folder during initial install 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.125 

* JambulaTV: Update UMEME power outages via scraper tool            i.e. jambulatv-umeme-outages-via-scraper 

* JambulaTV: Change the default DNS server IP address from Google's            8.8.8.8 to 8.8.4.4 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Home-Assistant Core to the latest Github version:            2021.6.6 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where multiple voice alerts and sounds are            processed at the same time leading to collisions 

* JambulaTV: Enable flapping when checking for availability of Bluez            devices in Icinga2 monitoring software 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Home-Assistant Core to the latest Github version:            2021.7.3 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Flexget to the latest development version:            3.1.133.dev 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade FFmpeg to the latest version: 4.4 (Rao) 

* JambulaTV: Update UMEME power outages via scraper tool            i.e. jambulatv-umeme-outages-via-scraper 

* JambulaTV: Add the following On-line based radio stations to the            Internet radio streamer tool 

* JambulaTV: Add support for reporting the Genre of music currently            playing to the FM radio streamer tool 

* JambulaTV: Add support for calling code (076) recently assigned to            MTN Uganda to our PBX telephone system i.e. Update the            Asterisk and FreePBX dialplan files: extensions.conf and            extensions_override_freepbx.conf respectively 

* JambulaTV: Update the music download tool i.e. 'jambulatv-fetch-music' 

* JambulaTV: Add support for reading of the current local time in a            requested world city using voice commands in Speech            Recognition (ASR) engine 

* JambulaTV: Fix a minor issue with the water supply tool i.e. Update            jambulatv-water-supply 

* JambulaTV: Refactor and rename the water supply reading tool from            'jambulatv-water-reading-today' to            'jambulatv-water-reading' and add ability to input not            only Today's water readings but also Yesterday and other            days 

* JambulaTV: Fix a minor issue with the water supply status tool i.e.            Update jambulatv-water-supply 

* JambulaTV: Fix issues with process locking in the sounds tool i.e.            Update 'jambulatv-sounds' 

* JambulaTV: Update the stream URL(s) for the following on-line based            radio station(s) in the Internet radio streamer tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Update the 'now playing' code in the FM radio streamer            tool i.e. 'jambulatv-fm-radio-streamer' as follows: 

* JambulaTV: Clean up GSM USSD controller tool i.e jambulatv-gsm-ussd-ug 

* JambulaTV: Extend voice notification support for home arrivals and            departures i.e. presence detection. Also indicate when            a user has been away for either a long or short time 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade system's Linux kernel to latest version: 5.4.137 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Pulseaudio sound system to version: 15.0 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade ALSA sound system libraries, plugins, utilities,            and OSS components to their latest versions as follows 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade icinga2 to the latest Github version: r2.13.0-1 

* JambulaTV: Rename custom Icinga2 object check command from 'systemd'            to 'systemd-jambula' so as to differentiate it from the            officially contributed check-systemd plugin 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Icinga2 Monitoring Plugins to the latest version:            2.3.1 

* JambulaTV: Add initial support for Icinga2 contributed plugins            e.g. check-systemd 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade icingaweb2 to the latest working version: 2.8.4 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Sphinxbase and Pocketsphinx to latest Github            versions 

* JambulaTV: Disable the use of Use Case Manager (UCM) feature in ALSA            sound system since it is not supported by soundcard i.e.            Add '-U' option to alsactl command 

* JambulaTV: Add new Icinga2 attribute 'flapping_ignore_states' to            the Bluez status template. This attribute allows for            ignoring of state changes to specified states during            the flapping calculation 

* JambulaTV: After upgrade of Pulseaudio, print a notice specifying any            additional tasks that are needed such as the re-install of            media related packages that use this library 

* JambulaTV: Re-order the install of libmpdclient library, which is a            dependency for both MPD daemon and MPC client 

* JambulaTV: Add support for playing on-the-fly FFmpeg generated sound            files located in the /tmp directory to the sounds tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-sounds' 

* JambulaTV: Switch to new project nickname: Nabusugwe 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 


Changes since v7.0
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Linux kernel to latest stable version: 5.10.3 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade ZoneMinder to the latest Github version: 1.35.16 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade icinga2 to latest github version: r2.12.3 

* JambulaTV: Update icingaweb2 sources to the latest github version 

* JambulaTV: Update jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer, the Internet            radio streamer tool as follows: 

* JambulaTV: Update jambulatv-fm-radio-streamer, the FM radio            streamer tool as follows: 

* JambulaTV: Fix several issues with the music download tool i.e.            Update 'jambulatv-fetch-music' 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade youtube-dl sources to latest version: 2021.01.08 

* JambulaTV: Update icinga2 plugin 'check_dvbt2_streams' in contributed            directory i.e. Add variable of 'TV_TYPE=DVB-T2' which is            used when testing to see if TV server is in use 

* JambulaTV: Add the default system sound audio output driver used by            various sound applications to the global settings file            i.e. Update the 'global_settings_configure' routines 

* JambulaTV: Use the audio driver specified in global settings file when            running the sounds tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-sounds' 

* JambulaTV: Use the audio driver specified in global settings file when            running Text2Speech tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-text2speech' 

* JambulaTV: Use the audio driver specified in global settings file when            running the FM radio streamer tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-fm-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Use the audio driver specified in global settings file when            running the Internet radio streamer tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Add new features and fix bugs in the water supply tool            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-water-supply' 

* JambulaTV: Allow Asterisk PBX user to login into system i.e. change            the shell from '/sbin/nologin' to '/bin/bash' 

* JambulaTV: Modify command used to get 'NETWORK_WIRELESS_TUNTAP_DEV'            variable in initial and main functions file 

* JambulaTV: Update system information tool i.e. jambulatv-sysinfo 

* JambulaTV: Improve the Internet radio and FM radio streamer tools i.e.            Update and fix bugs in 'jambulatv-internet-radio-streamer'            and 'jambulatv-fm-radio-streamer' 

* JambulaTV: Add the following variable declarations used by Internet,            FM radio streamers and other tools to the global settings            file: 

* JambulaTV: Remove stale PID file left behind by Internet radio streamer            tool when the Internet goes off i.e. Update the Internet/DNS            monitoring tool: jambulatv-dns-status-triggers 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Linux kernel to latest stable version: 5.10.10 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Pulseaudio sound system to version: 12.99.3 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade VLC Media Player to latest version: 3.0.12 

* JambulaTV: Include re-install of FluidSynth when upgrading PulseAudio            otherwise upgrade of other packages like VLC fail i.e. 

* JambulaTV: Permit asterisk user to run some commands as root e.g.            /usr/bin/grep 

* JambulaTV: Add 'parted' to list of allowed super user commands (sudo)            for multimedia user i.e. jambula 

* JambulaTV: Add support for installation of newer releases of curl 

* JambulaTV: Add voice notification support for ONLY vacation, holiday,            visitor, guest, quiet, and night modes.  Also add new            alerts for: 'Christmas season' mode, garbage collection day            assistance call for other rooms (porch, veranda, bedroom),            and when water supply is completely off 

* JambulaTV: Add support for SMARTD, the disk monitoring daemon 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Kodi to the latest github version of 18.9 (Leia) 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade youtube-dl sources to latest version: 2021.01.24.1 

* JambulaTV: Add setup of ALSA mixer levels (including Loopback and            Line-In controls) during initial install i.e. Add the            routines 'alsa_mixer_configure' to functions file, and            include it when configuring pulseaudio sound driver 

* JambulaTV: Update speaker volumes tool i.e. jambulatv-speaker-volume 

* JambulaTV: Drop the use of MPlayer when playing voice alerts. Instead            switch to using the MPV utility which is more reliable            i.e. Update sounds tool 'jambulatv-sounds' 

* JambulaTV: Drop the use of MPlayer when playing TTS generated voice            alerts. Instead switch to using the MPV utility which is            more reliable i.e.  Update the Text-2-Speech tool:            'jambulatv-text2speech' 

* JambulaTV: Fix time period announced after midnight by the sounds            tool i.e. Update 'jambulatv-sounds' 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue in which the water supply tool reports today's            water reading as missing, even when file exists locally            i.e. Update 'jambulatv-water-supply' 

* JambulaTV: Switch back to using Longterm Linux 5.4.x kernel versions            i.e. Downgrade to Linux 5.4.99 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Longterm Linux kernel sources to their latest            versions 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 


Changes since v6.9
--------------------

* JambulaTV: Improve code for the 'Now Playing' feature to allow for showing pretty song title and artist names for locally stored music tracks with no metadata 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Linux kernel to new stable version: 5.8.12 

* JambulaTV: Update GSM USSD controller tool i.e.jambulatv-gsm-ussd-ug 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where rtorrent systemd service does not halt all processes (i.e. rtorrent and screen) when stop iscalled 

* JambulaTV: Add new Python 3 dependency modules for Home-Assistantversion 0.115 to pips directory. These packages may berequired in future upgrade 

* JambulaTV: Disable OSD notification when checking for Internet connectivity. This is is because the OSD tool is slow, and during multiple queries leads to other notification processes being backloged 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Linux kernel to new stable version: 5.9.1 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Home-Assistant Core to the latest Github version:0.116.4 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Home-Assistant-CLI to latest Github version:0.10.0.dev20200827100801 

* JambulaTV: Ensure Home-Assistant starts only after mosquitto MQTTand kodi media services have been started i.e. Updatethe systemd unit file for home-assistant.service 

* JambulaTV: Update Home-Assistant configuration files 

* JambulaTV: Add Internet data saver mode support to the Internet/DNSmonitoring tool i.e. jambulatv-dns-status-trigger 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where kodi start up volumes are not fixed and vary per each restart 

* JambulaTV: Add support for bluetooth presence detection using Icinga2monitoring software 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade icingaweb2 to the latest github version: 2.8.2 

* JambulaTV: Add support for playback of external audio sources (likeCD, cassette player) via Line-In 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Linux kernel to latest stable version: 5.9.2 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade TVHeadend to latest version: 4.3-1914~g214a14f-dirty 

* JambulaTV: Fix issue where the API user for Icinga director is createdmultiple times during upgrades leading to Icinga2 service failing to start 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Home-Assistant Core to the latest Github version:0.117.1 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade OpenZWave sources to the latest Github
version:1.6-1392-gb0afd4c-dirty NOTE: This version is currently not compatible with Home-Assistant hence not being used 

* JambulaTV: Rename Home-Assitant install and configuration routines so they conform to change in upstream project name i.e.Project is now called 'Home-Assistant Core' 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Linux kernel to latest stable version: 5.9.6 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade v4l-utils package to the latest compatible version:v4l-utils-1.16.8 

* JambulaTV: Upgrade Flexget to the latest development version: 3.1.87.dev 

* JambulaTV: Switch to using ALSA audio output in the sounds tool i.eUpdate 'jambulatv-sounds' 

